# MCP Atlassian Docker Sample (Jira Server/DC)

This repository provides a ready-to-use Docker configuration for deploying the [sooperset/mcp-atlassian](https://github.com/sooperset/mcp-atlassian) integration with Atlassian Jira Server or Data Center.

## Prerequisites

- Docker installed on your machine
- Jira Server or Data Center instance (version 8.14+)
- A Personal Access Token (PAT) for your Jira instance

## Usage

1. **Create a `.env` file** in your project folder with the following content:

    ```env
    JIRA_URL=https://jira.your-company.com
    JIRA_PERSONAL_TOKEN=your_personal_token
    ```

    Replace the values with your Jira Server/DC URL and personal token.

2. **Run the Docker container:**

    ```bash
    docker run --rm -p 9000:9000 --env-file .env ghcr.io/sooperset/mcp-atlassian:latest --transport sse --port 9000 -vv
    ```

    - The server will be available at `http://localhost:9000/sse`
    - If you prefer the streamable-http transport, use `--transport streamable-http` and connect to `/mcp`.

## Example Configuration (JSON)

If you want to connect this to an IDE or automation, here’s a sample configuration block:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "mcp-atlassian": {
      "command": "docker",
      "args": [
        "run",
        "--rm",
        "-i",
        "-e", "JIRA_URL",
        "-e", "JIRA_PERSONAL_TOKEN",
        "ghcr.io/sooperset/mcp-atlassian:latest"
      ],
      "env": {
        "JIRA_URL": "https://jira.your-company.com",
        "JIRA_PERSONAL_TOKEN": "your_personal_token"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

